5:
Why are all the adults looking so
serious today? Light's even dressed
up too, for some reason.
8:
Oh, hey Stinelle. This is grown-up
stuff. Too boring for kids like you.
13:
I'll be the judge of that. Unlike the
low-end CPU crammed into your
head, I have a fully functioning
manabrain!
17:
That diss came outta nowhere!
What'd I ever do to you?!
21:
They're holding a ceremony to
celebrate finishing the Voluntas
Splice, and Stella's going to be the
representative for Starview.
26:
Ah, this is about that gigantic tower
you were all working on... I guess
that explains why Stella was all done
up too.
28:
You have to look the part if you're
going to attend a political event.
37:
Hehe, did you think looking cute was
my only specialty? This is actually
my area of expertise.
40:
I bet there's going to be plenty of
rich and powerful morons at this
ceremony.
44:
Oh Liiight, you'll bring me along too,
won't yoooou?
47:
If you don't... I'll keep rubbing your
head until all the fur comes off!
57:
Aaand that's enough of that! We're
trying to have a serious
conversation here. Kiddos like you
should be playing outside.
61:
Excuse me? That's rich, coming from
you. You're even younger than Shota!
65:
Excuse ME? At least I have a job as
Lilie's assistant. Run along now, little
rugrat. Go find some dirt to roll
around in.
70: What did you just say to me?!
74: Check it out! It's Brat vs. Mechabrat!
85:
*sigh* How boooring! Why is
everyone getting along?
88:
Starview Village, eh? I'd only heard
rumors up until now...
89:
The Academy and the Guild are
united on this. We know who's
coming out on top, so we'll follow...
92:
They clearly only sent out delegates
that could play nice.
96:
The dress I'm wearing deserves
better than their empty flattery.
Stella was at least sincere, but her
vocabulary leaves a lot to be
desired...
100:
Apologies, Stinelle. I've been so busy,
I haven't spared you a moment. Do
you want something to eat? I can
bring you a plate.
104:
Acting like you're my father or
something now? Keep this up and
you'll be known as Old Man Light by
the entire city.
108:
I think I'll leave you to ruminate with
the rest of the cattle while I go find
my OWN entertainment.
111: W-wait a moment. I can go wi—
115:
As much as my cuteness deserves
doting attention, you have a job to
do. So go do it.
122:
*sigh* I suppose it's nice that
everyone's chatting about their
hopes and dreams... But when's it
going to be my time to shine?
125:
The strongest one? Nimbus, for sure!
Have you seen those claws and
fangs of his?!
127:
Of course a musclehead like you
would say that. You think brute force
is gonna win you fights? He wouldn't
even beat Ryuichi.
129:
*sigh* This is insufferable. If only
Professor Reylas was here.
132:
Now those are some familiar
names. But what is this pointless
banter I am hearing?
135:
...And who're you? You from Starview
Village?
137:
There's a surprise! You can barely
rub two brain cells together, but at
least your intuition seems to be
working.
140:
Let me guess: you brats can't keep
up with adult conversation so you're
over here killing time. But surely you
can do better than this?
143:
You act as if you're not in the same
boat. Care to join in and suggest
something else, then?
145:
I'm tired of listening to these two
argue like children.
147:
You're the youngest of all of us! I'm a
grade above you in the Academy,
you know!
150:
Wow, she's right! You whine just like
a five-year-old would.
154:
But not to worry. I, in my unyielding
benevolence, shall entertain you
pathetic children.
157:
What... is this?! I've never seen
anything like this—even in Shibuya!
160:
Pick whichever one you like! I'll be
sure to explain the rules in a way
that even you can understand.
162:
Just don't expect to win against my
superior abilities though!
178:
Where's that big mouth of yours
now? You couldn't even beat Emma,
and she's the youngest of us!
182:
You want to go there, do you? Who
was the one crying helplessly just a
moment ago because he couldn't
take a single one of my pawns?
YOU! That's who!
185:
...That was fun. No one has pushed
me that far in chess before.
189:
I refuse to accept this. There must
be a bug in my programming! Or
something in the air! I'll win next
time!
192:
Hehe. I would be more than happy
play against you again.
198:
Excuse me? I refuse to play with
anyone who can't properly address
people by their names!
201:
Geez, you're annoying! Fine. Bye,
Luik. Bye, Emma. And... bye, Stinelle.
204:
It seems like you thoroughly enjoyed
yourself.
210:
Quiet, you... you silly bunny! Pathetic
excuse of a Champion! I could beat
you in a fight with nothing but my
fists!
221:
Were you able to become friends
with your new playmates?
227:
...Who knows? I suppose they did
prove more entertaining than my
servants.
231:
I might even consider granting them
the honor of a formal visit, so we
can play again. Would that... make
us friends?
240:
Come on, come on! We have to get
back soon or my mamas will give
me another boooring lecture!
242:
I have so much to tell them about
today!
